# Help function
multiplot <- function(..., plotlist=NULL, file, cols=1, layout=NULL) {
  #library(grid)

  # Make a list from the ... arguments and plotlist
  plots <- c(list(...), plotlist)

  numPlots = length(plots)

  # If layout is NULL, then use 'cols' to determine layout
  if (is.null(layout)) {
    # Make the panel
    # ncol: Number of columns of plots
    # nrow: Number of rows needed, calculated from # of cols
    layout <- matrix(seq(1, cols * ceiling(numPlots/cols)),
                    ncol = cols, nrow = ceiling(numPlots/cols))
  }

 if (numPlots==1) {
    print(plots[[1]])
  } else {
    # Set up the page
    grid.newpage()
    pushViewport(viewport(layout = grid.layout(nrow(layout), ncol(layout))))

    # Make each plot, in the correct location
    for (i in 1:numPlots) {
      # Get the i,j matrix positions of the regions that contain this subplot
      matchidx <- as.data.frame(which(layout == i, arr.ind = TRUE))

      print(plots[[i]], vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = matchidx$row,
                                      layout.pos.col = matchidx$col))
    }
  }
}

Clusterplot <- function(data0,n.pc,n.cluster,method='K-Means', scale=TRUE, outliers = TRUE){
  if (n.pc < 2){return ('Number of PC should be >= 2')}
  
  # Use first n.pc Principal Components to do analysis
  data = data0[,1:n.pc]

    
  if (scale==TRUE){
    # Center the mean to 0 and set the sd to 1
    data = scale(data,center=TRUE,scale = TRUE)
    }

  if (method == 'K-Means'){
    # Use K-Means model to do clustering
    set.seed(7002)
    km <- kmeans(data, n.cluster, iter.max = 1000, nstart = 10)
    pred <- as.character(km$cluster)}
  if (method == 'Hierarchical Clustering'){
    # Use Hierarchical Clustering to do clustering
    dist_mat <- dist(data[,1:n.pc], method = 'euclidean')
    hclust_avg <- hclust(dist_mat, method = 'average')
    pred <- as.character(cutree(hclust_avg, k = n.cluster))
  }
  
  if (outliers == TRUE){
    postfix = 'with Outliers'}else{
      postfix = 'without Outliers'
    }
  
    p <-ggplot(data=data.frame(Cluster=pred,data0),aes(x=PC1,y=PC2,color=Cluster,shape = Cluster)) +
    geom_point() + 
  scale_shape_manual(values=1:7) +
  labs(title=paste0(method,' With K =',n.cluster),
       subtitle = paste("First",n.pc,"PC's Used",postfix)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept=0, linetype="dashed", color = "black") + 
  geom_vline(xintercept=0, linetype="dashed", color = "black")
  return (p)
}
